  "description": [
    "EDITORIAL PAGE OF THE The Cauldron Seethes Keep America Out Clouds of murder bloodshed internecine strife and collapse of governmental leaders again obscure the con tinent of Europe This time the clouds hover in their blackest over little Austria where Chancellor Dollfuss has been murdered and members of his ministry detained as the result of a putsch by Nazis and Nazi sympathizers The situation in Vienna developed yesterday with startling rapidity Its movements since its inception have been so rapid that a clear analysis and appraisal is difficult if not impossible But the situation is sufficiently clear to indicate its grave portent and to cause alarm in the breast of all those who seek and who would maintain international peace It is sufficiently clear to cause rejoicing among Americans that we are on this side of the Atlantic Ocean It is sufficiently clear to sound with the voice of a Stentor a warning to America that it must maintain its policy of avoidance of the entanglements of European politics It is sufficiently clear to tell our American statesmen that they must remember that this nation is determined that regardless of what happens in Europe now America is going out of"
  ],
